            ],
            "text": "Solar thermal"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "collectors convert 60-70% of incident solar radiation to useful heat."
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "solar-pv"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Solar PV"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "converts 20-23% to electricity. On a per-square-metre basis, thermal is more efficient. But electricity is more flexible than hot water, it can power lights, appliances, or an immersion heater, charge a battery, run an EV, or be exported for income."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "UK annual yield comparison"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Solar thermal, 4 m² flat plate: approximately 1,400-1,800 kWh of useful heat per year (southern England). Provides 50-60% of a household's hot water over a full year."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Solar PV, 4 m² (approx 2 × 400 W panels = 0.8",
                    "marks": []
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Solar PV at 4 kWp (16-18 m²): 3,400-4,000 kWh/year of electricity, of which roughly half can be self-consumed directly."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When thermal makes sense"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Roof space is very limited (less than 6 m²), thermal delivers more heat per square metre than PV."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "High hot water demand (large family, no gas connection, immersion heater as primary source)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Already have a system installed with a compatible twin-coil cylinder."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why PV wins for most households"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "PV output can be diverted to hot water via an immersion diverter, replicating most of what thermal does."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "PV earns export income via the Smart Export Guarantee. Thermal cannot."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "PV is compatible with battery storage. Thermal excess in summer cannot be usefully stored."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Solar thermal requires a twin-coil cylinder and often a controller, pump, and expansion vessel. PV requires fewer ancillary components."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cost per"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                        "attrs": {
                          "termSlug": "kwp"
                        }
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "kWp"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "has fallen substantially for PV; solar thermal has not followed the same cost curve."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
